      "comment": "KEAYANG SUPREME (5) is a three-year-old filly from the Lee stable on debut. Showed some ability when a minor placegetter in a recent trial. Sure to be well educated and looks well placed to kick off with a win. MACHFREDDY (3) has been down the track in the last two outings in Victoria but did manage a second from this barrier three back at Mildura. The nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Go well. KATUNTI (2) copped a back row barrier when resuming at Horsham eight days ago but draws better so can show more. VINCENT ORILEY (4) is a three-year-old son of Vincent on debut for the Jim Barker yard. Was not far away in a recent trial. Keep safe at his first appearance.",
